<specimenCount box="[151,274,1140,1161]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="male">1 Male</specimenCount>
and female colour dimorphic; upperside of male golden-green, the lateral margins and apices of the elytra more or less copper or purple (
<figureCitation box="[400,473,1169,1190]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–95" captionStartId="91.[151,257,1609,1630]" captionTargetBox="[196,1386,233,1588]" captionTargetId="figure-168@91.[175,1419,191,1591]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="FIGURES 83–95. Melobasis spp. thoracica and pusilla species groups: 83–93. dorsal habitus: 83. M. thoracica Blackburn (♀ 4.3 mls. S.E. of Longford, Victoria); 84. M. thoracica Blackburn(♀ Lake Grace, W.A.); 85. M. duplexicolor sp. n. (♂ paratype, Rottnest Island, W.A.); 86. M. duplexicolor sp. n. (♀ paratype, Dongarra, W.A.); 87. M. inflammabilis Thomson (♀ Rottnest Island, W.A.); 88. M. pusilla Carter (♂ Slatey Creek, Edungalba, Queensland); 89. M. pusilla Carter (♀ Slatey Creek, Edungalba, Queensland); 90. M. parvula Carter (♂ Millstream, W.A.); 91. M. paucipunctata sp. n. (♂ paratype, 7 km N.E. of Wubin, W.A.); 92. M. paucipunctata sp. n. (♀ paratype, 7 km N.E. of Wubin, W.A.); 93. M. kunguluorum sp. n. (♀ holotype, Edungalba, Queensland).; 94–95. lateral margin of elytra: 94. M. duplexicolor sp. n.; 95. M. thoracica Blackburn. Scale bars of habitus images = 5.0 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 85</figureCitation>
); upperside of female yellow-bronze to brown-bronze, more or less suffused with copper or purple (
<figureCitation box="[232,305,1198,1219]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–95" captionStartId="91.[151,257,1609,1630]" captionTargetBox="[196,1386,233,1588]" captionTargetId="figure-168@91.[175,1419,191,1591]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="FIGURES 83–95. Melobasis spp. thoracica and pusilla species groups: 83–93. dorsal habitus: 83. M. thoracica Blackburn (♀ 4.3 mls. S.E. of Longford, Victoria); 84. M. thoracica Blackburn(♀ Lake Grace, W.A.); 85. M. duplexicolor sp. n. (♂ paratype, Rottnest Island, W.A.); 86. M. duplexicolor sp. n. (♀ paratype, Dongarra, W.A.); 87. M. inflammabilis Thomson (♀ Rottnest Island, W.A.); 88. M. pusilla Carter (♂ Slatey Creek, Edungalba, Queensland); 89. M. pusilla Carter (♀ Slatey Creek, Edungalba, Queensland); 90. M. parvula Carter (♂ Millstream, W.A.); 91. M. paucipunctata sp. n. (♂ paratype, 7 km N.E. of Wubin, W.A.); 92. M. paucipunctata sp. n. (♀ paratype, 7 km N.E. of Wubin, W.A.); 93. M. kunguluorum sp. n. (♀ holotype, Edungalba, Queensland).; 94–95. lateral margin of elytra: 94. M. duplexicolor sp. n.; 95. M. thoracica Blackburn. Scale bars of habitus images = 5.0 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 86</figureCitation>
); serrations of lateral margins of elytra well defined and acute (
<figureCitation box="[938,1011,1198,1219]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–95" captionStartId="91.[151,257,1609,1630]" captionTargetBox="[196,1386,233,1588]" captionTargetId="figure-168@91.[175,1419,191,1591]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="FIGURES 83–95. Melobasis spp. thoracica and pusilla species groups: 83–93. dorsal habitus: 83. M. thoracica Blackburn (♀ 4.3 mls. S.E. of Longford, Victoria); 84. M. thoracica Blackburn(♀ Lake Grace, W.A.); 85. M. duplexicolor sp. n. (♂ paratype, Rottnest Island, W.A.); 86. M. duplexicolor sp. n. (♀ paratype, Dongarra, W.A.); 87. M. inflammabilis Thomson (♀ Rottnest Island, W.A.); 88. M. pusilla Carter (♂ Slatey Creek, Edungalba, Queensland); 89. M. pusilla Carter (♀ Slatey Creek, Edungalba, Queensland); 90. M. parvula Carter (♂ Millstream, W.A.); 91. M. paucipunctata sp. n. (♂ paratype, 7 km N.E. of Wubin, W.A.); 92. M. paucipunctata sp. n. (♀ paratype, 7 km N.E. of Wubin, W.A.); 93. M. kunguluorum sp. n. (♀ holotype, Edungalba, Queensland).; 94–95. lateral margin of elytra: 94. M. duplexicolor sp. n.; 95. M. thoracica Blackburn. Scale bars of habitus images = 5.0 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 94</figureCitation>
); aedeagus less strongly widening from the basal piece to the widest point; apex of median lobe produced with the tip pointed (
<figureCitation box="[1023,1107,1228,1249]" captionStart="FIGURES 156–163" captionStartId="98.[151,258,1896,1917]" captionTargetBox="[342,1255,219,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-100@98.[315,1272,191,1884]" captionTargetPageId="98" captionText="FIGURES 156–163. Melobasis spp. thoracica and pusilla species groups:156–157. ovipositor: 156. M. thoracica Thomson (Little Anchorage, W.A.); 157. M. paucipunctata sp. n. (paratype, Wurarga, W.A.); 158–163. aedeagus: 158. M. thoracica Thomson (Eltham, Victoria); 159. M. duplexicolor sp. n. (paratype Rottnest Island, W.A.); 160. M. inflammabilis Thomson (Carnac Island, W.A.); 161. M. pusilla Carter (Edungalba, Queensland); 162. M. parvula Carter (Millstream, W.A.); 163. M. paucipunctata sp. n. (holotype Wurarga, W.A.). Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 159</figureCitation>
); S.W. 
