<keyLead pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
- Male and female not colour dimorphic; upperside largely reddish-violet, bluish-green or blackish-green (E. &amp; S. 
<collectingCountry box="[1333,1421,1286,1307]" name="Australia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Australia</collectingCountry>
) (
<figureCitation box="[232,303,1316,1337]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–95" captionStartId="91.[151,257,1609,1630]" captionTargetBox="[196,1386,233,1588]" captionTargetId="figure-168@91.[175,1419,191,1591]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="FIGURES 83–95. Melobasis spp. thoracica and pusilla species groups: 83–93. dorsal habitus: 83. M. thoracica Blackburn (♀ 4.3 mls. S.E. of Longford, Victoria); 84. M. thoracica Blackburn(♀ Lake Grace, W.A.); 85. M. duplexicolor sp. n. (♂ paratype, Rottnest Island, W.A.); 86. M. duplexicolor sp. n. (♀ paratype, Dongarra, W.A.); 87. M. inflammabilis Thomson (♀ Rottnest Island, W.A.); 88. M. pusilla Carter (♂ Slatey Creek, Edungalba, Queensland); 89. M. pusilla Carter (♀ Slatey Creek, Edungalba, Queensland); 90. M. parvula Carter (♂ Millstream, W.A.); 91. M. paucipunctata sp. n. (♂ paratype, 7 km N.E. of Wubin, W.A.); 92. M. paucipunctata sp. n. (♀ paratype, 7 km N.E. of Wubin, W.A.); 93. M. kunguluorum sp. n. (♀ holotype, Edungalba, Queensland).; 94–95. lateral margin of elytra: 94. M. duplexicolor sp. n.; 95. M. thoracica Blackburn. Scale bars of habitus images = 5.0 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
) or yellow-bronze to brown-bronze (S.W. 
<collectingCountry box="[721,811,1316,1337]" name="Australia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Australia</collectingCountry>
) (
<figureCitation box="[831,905,1316,1337]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–95" captionStartId="91.[151,257,1609,1630]" captionTargetBox="[196,1386,233,1588]" captionTargetId="figure-168@91.[175,1419,191,1591]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="FIGURES 83–95. Melobasis spp. thoracica and pusilla species groups: 83–93. dorsal habitus: 83. M. thoracica Blackburn (♀ 4.3 mls. S.E. of Longford, Victoria); 84. M. thoracica Blackburn(♀ Lake Grace, W.A.); 85. M. duplexicolor sp. n. (♂ paratype, Rottnest Island, W.A.); 86. M. duplexicolor sp. n. (♀ paratype, Dongarra, W.A.); 87. M. inflammabilis Thomson (♀ Rottnest Island, W.A.); 88. M. pusilla Carter (♂ Slatey Creek, Edungalba, Queensland); 89. M. pusilla Carter (♀ Slatey Creek, Edungalba, Queensland); 90. M. parvula Carter (♂ Millstream, W.A.); 91. M. paucipunctata sp. n. (♂ paratype, 7 km N.E. of Wubin, W.A.); 92. M. paucipunctata sp. n. (♀ paratype, 7 km N.E. of Wubin, W.A.); 93. M. kunguluorum sp. n. (♀ holotype, Edungalba, Queensland).; 94–95. lateral margin of elytra: 94. M. duplexicolor sp. n.; 95. M. thoracica Blackburn. Scale bars of habitus images = 5.0 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
); serrations of lateral margins of elytra often less well defined and obtuse (
<figureCitation box="[421,494,1345,1366]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–95" captionStartId="91.[151,257,1609,1630]" captionTargetBox="[196,1386,233,1588]" captionTargetId="figure-168@91.[175,1419,191,1591]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="FIGURES 83–95. Melobasis spp. thoracica and pusilla species groups: 83–93. dorsal habitus: 83. M. thoracica Blackburn (♀ 4.3 mls. S.E. of Longford, Victoria); 84. M. thoracica Blackburn(♀ Lake Grace, W.A.); 85. M. duplexicolor sp. n. (♂ paratype, Rottnest Island, W.A.); 86. M. duplexicolor sp. n. (♀ paratype, Dongarra, W.A.); 87. M. inflammabilis Thomson (♀ Rottnest Island, W.A.); 88. M. pusilla Carter (♂ Slatey Creek, Edungalba, Queensland); 89. M. pusilla Carter (♀ Slatey Creek, Edungalba, Queensland); 90. M. parvula Carter (♂ Millstream, W.A.); 91. M. paucipunctata sp. n. (♂ paratype, 7 km N.E. of Wubin, W.A.); 92. M. paucipunctata sp. n. (♀ paratype, 7 km N.E. of Wubin, W.A.); 93. M. kunguluorum sp. n. (♀ holotype, Edungalba, Queensland).; 94–95. lateral margin of elytra: 94. M. duplexicolor sp. n.; 95. M. thoracica Blackburn. Scale bars of habitus images = 5.0 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 95</figureCitation>
); aedeagus more strongly widening from the basal piece to the widest point; apex of median lobe produced with the tip rounded (
<figureCitation box="[528,612,1374,1395]" captionStart="FIGURES 156–163" captionStartId="98.[151,258,1896,1917]" captionTargetBox="[342,1255,219,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-100@98.[315,1272,191,1884]" captionTargetPageId="98" captionText="FIGURES 156–163. Melobasis spp. thoracica and pusilla species groups:156–157. ovipositor: 156. M. thoracica Thomson (Little Anchorage, W.A.); 157. M. paucipunctata sp. n. (paratype, Wurarga, W.A.); 158–163. aedeagus: 158. M. thoracica Thomson (Eltham, Victoria); 159. M. duplexicolor sp. n. (paratype Rottnest Island, W.A.); 160. M. inflammabilis Thomson (Carnac Island, W.A.); 161. M. pusilla Carter (Edungalba, Queensland); 162. M. parvula Carter (Millstream, W.A.); 163. M. paucipunctata sp. n. (holotype Wurarga, W.A.). Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 158</figureCitation>
); (female 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blackburn. B. Levey" authorityYear="1887" box="[709,833,1374,1395]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracica">
<emphasis box="[709,833,1374,1395]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">M. thoracica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
usually have the lateral margins of the pronotum more weakly convergent to the anterior and posterior angles than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Levey" authorityYear="2012" box="[747,899,1404,1425]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duplexicolor">
<emphasis box="[747,899,1404,1425]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">M. duplexicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
